ext and skills are discovered from both project-local sources (`AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, `.claude/skills/*`, `.codex/skills/*`, `.agents/skills/*`) and user-home globals (`~/.claude/CLAUDE.md`, `~/.claude/skills/*`, `~/.
codex/skills/*`, `~/.pipy/skills/*`) so the section listing matches what Pi shows when global resources are present. Chrome rendering is shared between the no-tool and bounded tool-loop sessions through `pipy_harness.nat
ive.chrome`. |
