 providers; `effort` is the configured reasoning effort label (`default` until per-model effort selection is wired). `proposal ready` / `verify ready` user-state signals are appended after the effort label so they stay v
isible without breaking the Pi-shape layout. The default `pipy` invocation auto-picks an available real provider, so the bottom status surfaces `(provider) model • effort` rather than `fake/fake-native-bootstrap` wheneve
r credentials are configured. The slash-menu input adapter additionally draws this same bottom block below the live input area so the user sees the status line directly below the prompt while typing. |
