th the input with names, dim descriptions, reverse-video selection highlight, Up/Down navigation, Enter to submit the selected command, Tab to accept without submitting, and Esc to close. The next fall-throughs are optio
nal prompt-toolkit input with slash-command completion (descriptions through `display_meta`), explicit file/path completion, completion-only `@file` reference labels, and multiline entry; then the stdlib `readline` adapt
er for Tab discovery without a runtime dependency; then plain stdin/stderr for captured streams. Richer editor behavior (history, resize-resilient TUI, mouse selection) remains deferred. |
